InclusionRules.name: Must be observed for at least 365d prior and alive on next day
Medical care. At least one outpatient visit and one filled prescription in [t0-365, t0-2], excluding lab claims, to  assure regular contact with medical care.
Terminal illness. Not in hospice for the period [t0-365,t0-1] or diagnosis indicating terminal illness.

Long-term care. Not in a nursing home in [t0-365, t0-1], except stays <30 days following hospital discharge. No  hospital discharge in [t0-365,t0-1] for a stay >30 days, which could indicate long-term care
Atrial fibrillation dose. Approved dose for atrial fibrillation. Apixaban 2.5 or 5mg, twice/day, rivaroxaban 15 or  20mg once/day
New user. For [t0-365, t0], no other filled prescription for any oral anticoagulant.
Atrial fibrillation. Diagnosis atrial fibrillation/flutter in [t0-90, t0-1].
Mitral valve stenosis. No diagnosis mitral valve stenosis in [t0-365, t0-1].

Reversible AF. No evidence in [t0-30, t0-1] of frequent causes of reversible or transient atrial fibrillation: diagnosis  of hyperthyroidism or open coronary artery bypass graft/open cardiac valve surgery
Other indication. No evidence [t0-30, t0-1] other oral anticoagulant indication: DVT/PE, hip or knee replacement,  femur/tibia/patella fracture, thrombectomy, chronic hypercoagulable state.
Severe CKD. No Medicare ESRD enrollment basis or diagnosis in [t0-365, t0-1] of severe chronic kidney disease  (CKD): stage 4/5/ESRD.
Stroke/SE. No stroke/systemic embolism in [t0-30, t0-1], as defined in §2. A single clot can spawn multiple emboli and thus lead to readmissions.
Major bleed. No anticoagulant-related bleeding hospitalization in [t0-30, t0-1], as defined in §2, which avoids confusion of new bleeds with continuing treatment for a prior outcome
